         <abstract>
            <p>A method for calculating the strict Chebyshev solution of overdetermined systems of linear equations using linear programming techniques is described. This method provides: (1) a way to determine, for the majority of cases, all the equations belonging to the characteristic set, (2) an efficient method to obtain the inverse of the matrix needed to calculate the strict Chebyshev solution, and (3) a way of recognizing when an element of the Chebyshev solution equals a corresponding element of the strict Chebyshev solution. As a result, in general, the computational effort is considerably reduced. Also the present method deals with full rank as well as rank deficient cases. Numerical results are given.</p>
          </abstract>
